body:
@pubkey hm, I just tried this in a graphQL replication test and I'm pretty sure I'm seeing the same thing. I feel like I'm stumbling around these tests a bit, so here is the code I used:

```
                await c.insert(schemaObjects.humanWithTimestamp({id: 'a123456', name: '1'}));

                await waitUntil(() => pushCount === 1);

                await c.incrementalUpsert({id: 'a123456', name: '2'})
                await c.incrementalUpsert({id: 'a123456', name: '3'})

                await waitUntil(() => pushCount === 3);

                const docsOnServer = server.getDocuments()[0];
                assert.strictEqual(docsOnServer.name, '3');
```

in this the assert is getting `1` vs. the expected `3`.

```
AssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: Expected values to be strictly equal:

'1' !== '3'
```
